<br>
I really, really liked Eddings work.  I wouldn't go as far to say its childish, there are some pretty adult themes in there.  But the storyline is excellent, and its not drawn out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The series I'm reading right now is Terry Goodkind's sword of truth series.  A VERY good morality play, a good twist and turn somewhere along the line.  If you're a sucker for drama (me!!) and have been known to cry sometimes while reading books, then you're in for a treat <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If you like that sort of thing, anyway.<br>
<br>
-Leavandor Sires <p><i>Felwithe born and bred, went to PoG and killed 'em all dead!<br>
